    <section class="container">
        <div class="content">
            <h1>Chapter 1</h1>
            <p>The Civil Rights Movement was a courageous struggle against oppression, fought by individuals who believed in the inherent dignity and equality of every human being. Through their unwavering determination and peaceful resistance, they paved the way for a more just and inclusive society.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="container">
        <div class="content">
            <h1>Chapter 2</h1>
            <p>From the Montgomery Bus Boycott to the Selma to Montgomery marches, the Civil Rights Movement was a powerful display of collective action. Ordinary people, fueled by a burning desire for justice, joined together to challenge discriminatory laws and social norms, leaving an indelible mark on history.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="container">
        <div class="content">
            <h1>Chapter 3</h1>
            <p>The Civil Rights Movement was not just a fight for legal rights; it was a battle for hearts and minds. Through their impassioned speeches, peaceful demonstrations, and acts of civil disobedience, activists confronted the conscience of a nation, compelling it to confront its deep-rooted prejudices and strive for true equality.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="container">
        <div class="content">
            <h1>Chapter 4</h1>
            <p>The Civil Rights Movement stands as a testament to the power of unity. African Americans, alongside allies of all races and backgrounds, formed an unbreakable bond, marching hand in hand towards a shared vision of a future where skin color would no longer determine one's worth or opportunities.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="container">
        <div class="content">
            <h1>Chapter 5</h1>
            <p>Despite facing violence, intimidation, and systemic opposition, the Civil Rights Movement persisted. Its leaders taught us that the pursuit of justice requires courage, resilience, and an unwavering belief in the power of nonviolence to effect lasting change.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

